A body was found Tuesday evening near a high school in Northeast Washington, the police said. The body, which appeared to be that of a man, was found by a passerby just before 6 p.m. near H.D. Woodson High School, which is in the 500 block of 55th Street NE, according to officer Hugh Carew, a police spokesman. No information was available about any cause of death. Police said they were conducting a death investigation.